</span><hr size=1> I've have seen  the FAQ and know I should work toward a full suit of crusty armor but I was needing help in what weapons to get.  I want to keep all my weapon skills up so I quess I am looking for weapons with low delay on them.  I have about 4k to 5k to play with.  Thx. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilzalot>Kilzalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/02 4:07:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4732.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapons for a starting tank</span><hr size=1> Lammy and Wurmslayer maybe.  Should be able to get both of those for 4-5k I would think. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->[65 Overlord]<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132589">Veteran Kilzalot Drachonis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
