<br>
1hand slashers:<br>
Wakiazashi of the Frozen Skies<br>
Lamentation<br>
Centi Longsword<br>
Centi Shortsword<br>
Black Blade of Tormenting<br>
Short Sword the Ykesha<br>
Elder Wolf Jawbone<br>
Shaded Longsword<br>
Wurmslayer<br>
<br>
Any of those will be very effective and rather within your budget.<br>
<br>
1hand blunt:<br>
Cane of the Tranquil<br>
Enamelled Black Mace<br>
Blackjack<br>
Mudman Enforcer<br>
Runed Branding Iron<br>
Iksar Beserker Club<br>
Maybe the Guard Captain's Mallet, if it's dropping in price on your server as much as mine. Or Jade Mace, which is also dirt cheap these days.<br>
<br>
Any of those should be within your budget or ability to get. Or just try and snag a rotting Goranga Spiked Club.<br>
<br>
Piercing:<br>
Either get something small and fast, like one of these:<br>
<br>
Shaded Dagger<br>
Walrus Fang<br>
Dragoon Dirk<br>
<br>
Or get a Centi Warspear, as they tend to be REALLY cheap these days, and are rather effective.<br>
<br>
2hand slashing:<br>
<br>
Blackened Alloy Bastard Sword is still a relatively useful weapon for skillups and a classic.<br>
Arbitor's Combine Greatsword<br>
Weighty Polearm<br>
<br>
2hand blunt:<br>
Sarnak Battlehammer? Whatever that 30/40 is that's rather cheap. Or just a shovel.<br>
<br>
All of that stuff should be withing your budget. Some of them are more effective than others (like CoT is better than a runed branding iron, but for skillups, both do the job well enough). So try and snag two to four quality weapons to use as main damage weapons and just fill out the rest of the slots with stuff that works for training. And train with them whenever you get a chance.<br>
<br>
Good luck. Have fun.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abividad>Abividad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/24/02 8:27:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4732.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: some cheapies</span><hr size=1> I didn't see you state your level, but you said starting tank, so I'm going to assume 20ish.<br>
<br>
The one hand slash listed would all work. I'd also incluse jagged blade of tormenting. It's a 13/25 weapon with + double digits, I forget exactly how much to dex, which will allow you to learn other one hand weapon (piercing, one hand blunt) skills a little faster.<br>
<br>
For one hand blunt, I'd add a Smoldering Brand. 9/22 and procs 14 hp burn at level 1.<br>
<br>
Piercing, a Jarinth ( I know I spelled that wrong, sorry, but you'll be able to figure it out looking at Bazaar window) Trident is 11/22. I tried an Agressor dirk, which had a delay of 20, but damage was only 6 so I stopped using it<br>
<br>
two hand blunt, I skilled up with the Black Alloy Bastard Sword, which was given to me as I sat next to the dock in Halas and fished. The Polearm (29/34 at level 53 I think) has a good delay, but the damage scales down the lower level you are. look at one in bazaar and it will tell you the stats it will have when you wield it.<br>
<br>
I have Sarnak Battlehammer also, well under 500pp on Povar. Another good 2hb is a granite facegrinder 29/34 if I remember right. I needed to raise money, and the price has dropped a lot on my server, I was able to get 2k for it when I sold it.<br>
<br>
Something to remember. You'll reach weapon skills cap at level 40 when you get to 200. no more increases till 50, so you have plenty of time to catch up skills that are lagging then. When in a good group, ask if it's ok to practice some of your less used skills<br>
<br>
